<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Brush fires in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> torched houses and forced the evacuation of several communities, and <LOCATION> Idaho </LOCATION>'s governor declared a state of extreme emergency to handle the blazes consuming thousands of acres of forest. A fast-moving fire roared through a windy tinderbox of dry grass and brush in the <LOCATION> Sierra </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION> foothills today, and Sheriff's Lt. <PERSON> Greg </PERSON> <PERSON> Burton </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Fresno </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, said at least three homes had been destroyed, with 1,500 firefighters unable to control the 3,000-acre fire. At least 2,500 residents were evacuated from the communities of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Auberry </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Meadow </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lakes </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Alder </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Springs </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Bald </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mountain </LOCATION> and <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Basin </PERSON>, said <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Kutz </PERSON>, spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Forestry </ORGANIZATION>. About 150 nursing home patients were among those taken to a local high school in the area 190 miles east of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION>. One of the evacuees, <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> <PERSON> Burnham </PERSON>, had moved to the highland area from low-lying <LOCATION> Fresno </LOCATION> just a day before the fire _ to escape the heat. When a sheriff's deputy screamed at him to clear out of his new house, <PERSON> Burnham </PERSON> said, `` I never even came out with a shirt.'' Elsewhere in central <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, firefighters saved at least a dozen homes from a fire that burned 10,500 acres near the city of <LOCATION> Atascadero </LOCATION>. `` Miraculously, all those homes have been spared,'' <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Forestry </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> <PERSON> Alsop </PERSON> said. `` The flames burned right up to them.'' About 750 firefighters had the blaze 40 percent contained early today. Officials refused to estimate when it might be fully contained, although increasing humidity and low overnight temperatures were a boon to firefighters, <PERSON> Alsop </PERSON> said. The blaze destroyed 15 to 20 outbuildings, including barns and corrals. Owners moved animals from some ranches in the area about 175 miles north of <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. In the <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> area community of Walnut, firefighters surrounded a fast-moving brush fire that had threatened several homes and the nearby <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Polytechnical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Pomona </LOCATION>, officials said. Campus police evacuated 800 students as the fire approached, said <PERSON> Rafael </PERSON> <PERSON> Ortiz </PERSON>, a firefighter with the <ORGANIZATION> Los </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Angeles </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>, but the blaze was contained about 8:30 p.m. and students were allowed back into their dorm rooms on the campus 30 miles east of downtown <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. In <LOCATION> Idaho </LOCATION>, Gov. <PERSON> Cecil </PERSON> <PERSON> Andrus </PERSON> authorized military reinforcements Friday to join the battle against hundreds of forest fires. His emergency proclamation allows the state to use the National Guard. The <ORGANIZATION> Boise </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Interagency </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATIO