<HEAD>Priest Says Racism Permeates Catholic Church in U.S.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILWAUKEE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Racism permeates the <ORGANIZATION> Roman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, several clerics said, warning that more blacks could follow the lead of a priest who set up an unauthorized African American congregation. Seven black church leaders, speaking Friday after a national conference of black clergy, called on the church to address the needs of minorities and move blacks to positions of authority. `` The church has bought into the racist practices of the American culture,'' said the Rev. <PERSON> Victor </PERSON> <PERSON> Cohea </PERSON>, a pastor from <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Orleans </LOCATION>. The news conference at <ORGANIZATION> Marquette </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> followed a joint conference of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Clergy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Caucus </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sisters </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Conference </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Seminarians </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>. Much discussed was the case of the Rev. <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Stallings </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION>, priest who was suspended for setting up an independent African-American congregation without permission of his archbishop. The Rev. <PERSON> Albert </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> McKnight </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Opelousas </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> La. </LOCATION>, warned that others could follow <PERSON> Stallings </PERSON>' lead. `` We're ready to