<HEAD>Rockets Kill 12 in Kabul Attacks at Bazaar, Elsewhere</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By EDITH M. LEDERER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>KABUL, Afghanistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A barrage of rockets fired by Moslem guerrillas slammed into <LOCATION> Kabul </LOCATION> on Saturday, with one spraying shrapnel and glass around a crowded bazaar. At least 14 people were killed in the attacks, official <ORGANIZATION> Radio </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kabul </ORGANIZATION> said. <ORGANIZATION> Foreign </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Mohammad </PERSON> <PERSON> Nabi </PERSON> <PERSON> Amani </PERSON> said the U.S.-backed guerrillas are stepping up such attacks to give them more leverage before Monday's U.S.-Soviet talks on <LOCATION> Afghanistan </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Stockholm </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Sweden </LOCATION>. The Soviets, who fought alongside Afghan government troops for nine years, are the Marxist government's major arms supplier. <PERSON> Amani </PERSON> said 12 people were killed Saturday. He said eight people died and 40 were injured when the rocket hit the bazaar. Other rockets landed around the center and south of the capital, killing four people and injuring 16, he said. Official Radio <LOCATION> Kabul </LOCATION> said 14 people were killed and 50 injured in the attacks. The broadcast was monitored in <LOCATION> Islamabad </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION>. Diplomatic sources speaking on condition of anonymity said they counted 30 rockets fired Saturday. In the past month, the rebels, who call themselves <ORGANIZATION> Mujahedeen </ORGANIZATION> or Islamic holy warriors, have been launching long-range rockets from behind the hills that ring this mile-high capital. More than 200 people have died, virtually all civilians. <PERSON> Abdul </PERSON> <PERSON> Halim </PERSON>, a 50-year-old school employee who suffered shrapnel wounds, said he was walking across the street when the rocket exploded at the <LOCATION> Kote </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sangi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bazaar </LOCATION> in western <LOCATION> Kabul </LOCATION>. `` Whoever fired the rocket, they are anti-Moslem