Roman Catholics, although a large number of them do not regularly attend church. In the past, some party members were known to have been Catholics, but they rarely dared to profess their beliefs in public. `` Making the free exercise of religion complete, the dialogue between Marxists and the faithful should continue on the highest level,'' <PERSON> Berecz </PERSON> said. Pope <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> II </PERSON> plans to visit <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> for the first time in 1991, and diplomatic relations with the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> may be re-established soon. The dramatic police changes may be an attempt by the party to polish up its image prior to next year's first multiparty elections in <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> since 1948. Party leaders decided Friday to hold the party's congress Oct. 6, a day earlier than originally scheduled. The goal of the meeting is to unite divided party members and chart winning policies for the 1990 elections.
