<BYLINE>By LOUIS MEIXLER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Israeli leaders on Saturday dismissed criticism of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s abduction of a pro-Iranian Moslem cleric and said he led a `` fanatical'' group that had launched terrorist attacks on <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Sheik </PERSON> <PERSON> Abdul </PERSON> <PERSON> Karim </PERSON> <PERSON> Obeid </PERSON>, allegedly linked to the capture of <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> soldiers in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> and the kidnapping of a <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marine </ORGANIZATION> held hostage there, was abducted Friday from his south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> home and taken to <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> in a helicopter. `` There may be some people who voice disapproval, but public opinion will understand that this act was taken against one of the leaders of one of the most fanatical groups in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>,'' said Prime Minister <PERSON> Yitzhak </PERSON> <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>'s spokesman, <PERSON> Avi </PERSON> <PERSON> Pazner </PERSON>. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> officials have said <PERSON> Obeid </PERSON> is a leader of the Iranian-backed <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Obeid </PERSON> has denied belonging to the group. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> radio reported Saturday that <PERSON> Sheikh </PERSON> <PERSON> Abbas </PERSON> <PERSON> Musawi </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION> leader who lives in a southern suburb of <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>, said the organization will not agree to a prisoner exchange and will increase attacks on <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>. The fundamentalist <ORGANIZATION> Islamic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION> advocates the destruction of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> and its replacement by an Iranian-style Islamic state. In <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> on Saturday, <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> Secretary-General <PERSON> Javier </PERSON> <PERSON>